trans-unit.source: Thrown when a ZIP file does not contain any .xml files
trans-unit.target: Thrown when a ZIP file does not contain any .xml files

trans-unit.source: This exception occurs when the custom module zip package does not contain any module definition (.xml) files.
trans-unit.target: This exception occurs when the custom module zip package does not contain any module definition (.xml) files.

trans-unit.source: These files need to reside in the root of the zip package (e.g. not within a subfolder.)
trans-unit.target: These files need to reside in the root of the zip package (e.g. not within a subfolder.)

trans-unit.source: Verify that one or more xml module definition files are in the root folder of the zip package by extracting it to a temporary folder on your disk drive.
trans-unit.target: Verify that one or more xml module definition files are in the root folder of the zip package by extracting it to a temporary folder on your disk drive.

trans-unit.source: Any xml files should be directly in the folder you extracted the zip package to.
trans-unit.target: Any xml files should be directly in the folder you extracted the zip package to.

trans-unit.source: Make sure when you create the zip package that you do not simply select a folder that contains xml files to zip as this will create a sub folder within the zip package with the same name as the folder you selected to zip.
trans-unit.target: Make sure when you create the zip package that you do not simply select a folder that contains xml files to zip as this will create a sub folder within the zip package with the same name as the folder you selected to zip.
